<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-09-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-09-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1152" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1152">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/907.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 6, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The American Consul at Nogales recommends that 500 rifles and 150,000
                            rounds ammunition be supplied to consular agent, Cananea, immediately
                            for protection of American life and property. I respectfully request
                            your telegraphic authorization to forward this shipment.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>